FIVE people were killed while two sustained serious injuries when two vehicles collided head-on between Aliwal North and Queenstown in the Eastern Cape on Wednesday, 27 July. Eastern Cape Transport spokesman, Unathi Binqose, said an Isuzu double cab with two men and three woman collided with a mini-truck carrying two men. “All five occupants from the Isuzu double cab died on the scene, while both occupants from the Nissan UD Truck were entrapped and severely injured,” said Binqose in a statement. ALSO WATCH: Armed robbers killed in shoot-out with cops! He said the dead were all from Ikhala TVET College in Queenstown. “These are not just numbers. It’s our sisters and brothers, cousins, your friends,” he said. Sunday World reported that one of the dead was the cousin of one of the department’s road engineers, while the two of the deceased were cousins to one of the managers at the department. 